HEADWORD: Endecane
<hw>En"de*cane</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/
eleven.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>One of the higher hydrocarbons of
the <isa>paraffin</isa> series, <chform>C11H24</chform>, found as a
constituent of petroleum.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>hendecane</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Endecaphyllous</ent>⟦br⟧
